	<main id="inner-wrap" class="wrap kt-clear" role="main">
		<div id="primary" class="content-area">
	<div class="content-container site-container">
		<div id="main" class="site-main">
						<div class="content-wrap">
				<article id="post-80574" class="entry content-bg single-entry post-80574 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-christmas-recipes category-cookies-bars-recipes category-italian-dessert-recipes category-sicilian-recipes">
	<div class="entry-content-wrap">
		<header class="entry-header post-title title-align-inherit title-tablet-align-inherit title-mobile-align-inherit">
	<nav id="breadcrumbs" aria-label="breadcrumbs"><span><span><a href="https://coleycooks.com/">Home</a></span> » <span><a href="https://coleycooks.com/recipe-index/">Recipes</a></span> » <span><a href="https://coleycooks.com/category/cookies-bars-recipes/">Cookies + Cakes</a></span></span></nav><h1 class="entry-title">Sicilian Chocolate Spice Cookies</h1><div class="entry-meta entry-meta-divider-dot">
	<span class="posted-by"><span class="meta-label">By</span><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://coleycooks.com/about/">Nicole Gaffney</a></span></span>					<span class="updated-on">
						<time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2025-12-04T16:45:30-05:00" itemprop="dateModified">December 4, 2025</time>					</span>
					<!-- [element-19043] -->
<span class="kt-adv-heading19043_6f1f25-e4 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading19043_6f1f25-e4"><a href="#wprm-recipe-container-80590" data-recipe="80590" style="color: #333333;" class="wprm-recipe-jump wprm-recipe-link wprm-jump-to-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal">Jump to Recipe</a></span>
<!-- [/element-19043] --></div><!-- .entry-meta -->
</header><!-- .entry-header -->

<div class="entry-content single-content">
	
<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p>These Italian&nbsp;<strong>chocolate spice cookies</strong>&nbsp;are soft, tender, and warm with spices that instantly taste like the holidays. They're simple to make, filled with nostalgia and perfect for sharing all season long.</p><!-- [element-19046] -->
<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>This post may contain affiliate links.</em></p>
<!-- [/element-19046] -->



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1799" fetchpriority="high" data-pin-url="https://coleycooks.com/chocolate-spice-cookies/?tp_image_id=80579" data-pin-title="Sicilian Chocolate Spice Cookies" src="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-16.jpg" alt="Frosted chocolate spice cookies arranged on parchment paper, each topped with a walnut half." data-skip-lazy data-skip-lazy class="wp-image-80579" srcset="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-16.jpg 1200w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-16-200x300.jpg 200w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-16-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-16-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-16-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-16-720x1079.jpg 720w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-16-360x540.jpg 360w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-16-180x270.jpg 180w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-16-150x225.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p>These chocolate spice cookies have been a staple Christmas cookie in my family forever, but I only recently found out they're actually a traditional Sicilian cookie. </p>



<p>They're known as tetu, tutu, toto or other variations depending on the region or city.&nbsp;</p>



<p>They're simple, but comforting and always taste like Christmas. The second I take a bite, I'm flooded with the best memories of childhood and family.</p>



<p>Growing up, my cousins and I always made fun of the chocolate spice cookies since they were boring compared to all of the other more enticing treats. </p>



<p>I admit, I was one of the biggest haters! But over the years I've come to actually really love them.&nbsp;</p>



<p>If you're looking for a simple, classic Italian cookie to bake this Christmas season, let this one be it!</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" id="h-what-are-italian-toto-cookies">What are Italian Toto Cookies?</h2>



<p>Toto cookies are traditional Italian chocolate spice ball cookies that go by many names depending on where you are in Italy. You'll see them called tetù, teta, totò and sometimes meatball cookies because of their round shape and brown color.&nbsp;</p>



<p>They're traditionally made in Sicily for All Saints' Day on November 1 and All Souls' Day or Day of the Dead on November 2 as a way to honor loved ones who have passed. In Italian-American communities they're typically served around Christmastime. &nbsp;</p>



<p>You'll find different versions of tetù cookies all across Sicily, with each region having its own take. Some lean heavier on spices with a simple sugar or chocolate glaze, while others include orange zest, nuts, raisins or sprinkles.</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="801" data-pin-url="https://coleycooks.com/chocolate-spice-cookies/?tp_image_id=80580" data-pin-title="Sicilian Chocolate Spice Cookies" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1200&#039;%20height=&#039;801&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201200%20801&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A frosted chocolate spice cookie topped with a walnut half, surrounded by more cookies in soft focus." class="wp-image-80580 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-17.jpg" data-srcset="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-17.jpg 1200w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-17-300x200.jpg 300w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-17-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-17-768x513.jpg 768w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-17-720x481.jpg 720w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-17-360x240.jpg 360w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-17-180x120.jpg 180w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-17-150x100.jpg 150w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></figure>



<p>My family's version is pretty traditional. We often add chocolate chips, and sometimes add little chopped up bits of walnut, which is my favorite. </p>



<p>The cookies with nuts always get a whole walnut placed on top of the icing to indicate which cookies have nuts and which do not.</p>



<p>The only thing we do differently in my family is the icing. The original icing recipe never really worked well for us, so my Aunt Ang started using the one on the back of the Hershey's cocoa container instead. It's not exactly traditional, but we think it's much better!</p>



<p>This recipe makes a lot of cookies and, believe it or not, the original recipe was actually double the size. I guess that tracks considering my grandma had 12 siblings!</p>



<p id="isPasted">You can cut the recipe in half again to make an even smaller batch, but I think you're better off having a few extra to bring to parties or share with friends and family.</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_0b9a05-a8"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<p class="has-text-align-center">Want more&nbsp;<strong>classic Italian dessert recipes?</strong>&nbsp;Try my classic&nbsp;<a href="https://coleycooks.com/ricotta-cheesecake/">Ricotta Cheesecake</a>, these soft and chewy&nbsp;<a href="https://coleycooks.com/pignoli-cookies/">Pignoli Cookies</a>&nbsp;or this rich chocolate almond&nbsp;<a href="https://coleycooks.com/torta-caprese/">Torta Caprese recipe</a>.</p>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_8c5a65-dd"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<h2 class="kt-adv-heading80574_4689d8-64 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading80574_4689d8-64">Why This Recipe Works</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>My family's version of a traditional Italian cookie recipe that tastes like Christmas.</li>



<li>Makes up to 4 dozen cookies to share with friends and family.</li>



<li>They freeze really well, both the dough or fully baked and frosted cookies.</li>



<li>Easily customizable with different add-ins and toppings like walnuts, chocolate chips and sprinkles.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" data-pin-url="https://coleycooks.com/chocolate-spice-cookies/?tp_image_id=80582" data-pin-title="Sicilian Chocolate Spice Cookies" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1200&#039;%20height=&#039;1800&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201200%201800&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Overhead view of labeled ingredients including flour, sugar, cocoa powder, spices, eggs, butter, Crisco, oil, milk, vanilla, powdered sugar, and walnuts." class="wp-image-80582 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Labeled-INGREDIENTS-10.png" data-srcset="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Labeled-INGREDIENTS-10.png 1200w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Labeled-INGREDIENTS-10-200x300.png 200w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Labeled-INGREDIENTS-10-683x1024.png 683w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Labeled-INGREDIENTS-10-768x1152.png 768w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Labeled-INGREDIENTS-10-1024x1536.png 1024w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Labeled-INGREDIENTS-10-720x1080.png 720w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Labeled-INGREDIENTS-10-360x540.png 360w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Labeled-INGREDIENTS-10-180x270.png 180w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Labeled-INGREDIENTS-10-150x225.png 150w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_16a311-78"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_7ee72d-77"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<h2 class="kt-adv-heading80574_aa8ac7-15 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading80574_aa8ac7-15">Italian Spice Cookie Ingredients</h2>



<p><strong>Crisco or butter</strong>&nbsp;- Our classic family recipe uses vegetable shortening which gives the cookies their soft, tender texture, but butter can also be used. Butter adds a richer flavor, but has a slightly denser crumb since it contains some water versus shortening which is 100% fat. </p>



<p><strong>Flour</strong>&nbsp;- Use regular all purpose flour and measure it carefully to avoid a dry or sticky dough. Always spoon flour into your cup, rather than scooping, then level off the top.</p>



<p><strong>Cocoa powder</strong>&nbsp;- Use unsweetened Dutch process cocoa powder. If using unprocessed raw cacao, you will need to use baking soda instead of baking powder. Higher quality cocoa will give these cookies a better chocolate flavor, but any kind will work.&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>Spices</strong>&nbsp;- Ground cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves are essential to giving these cookies their signature spice. Make sure your spices are fresh for the best flavor. They all work together to give the cookies that classic holiday warmth.</p>



<p><strong>Nuts</strong>&nbsp;- The walnuts are totally optional, but I love them with nuts and prefer them this way. You can also add nuts to half and leave the other half plain which is what we usually do. Place a whole walnut or more chopped nuts on top of the frosting to let people know which cookies contain nuts.</p>



<p><strong>Chocolate chips</strong>&nbsp;- Also optional, but recommended for a bit more texture and richness, especially if you like little bits of chocolate throughout the cookies.</p>



<p><strong>Baking powder</strong>&nbsp;- Make sure it's fresh so the cookies puff properly. If using a raw cacao powder, you will want to swap this out for baking soda.</p>



<p><strong>Sugars&nbsp;</strong>- You will need confectioners' sugar for the icing in addition to granulated sugar for the cookies.&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>Salt</strong>&nbsp;- I use Diamond Crystal Kosher salt, which is less salty than other brands. You may need to adjust to taste.</p>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_99f4fb-90"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<p class="has-text-align-center">*Find the <strong>full ingredient list</strong> in the <strong>recipe card</strong> below!</p>
</div></div>
</div></div>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_775bd8-61"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<h2 class="kt-adv-heading80574_5b50dc-94 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading80574_5b50dc-94">Helpful Equipment</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><a class="tasty-link" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-tasty-links-no-disclosure href="https://amzn.to/3r9AyPe">Mixing bowls</a></li>



<li><a class="tasty-link" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-tasty-links-no-disclosure href="https://amzn.to/49ikICY">Electric mixer</a> or <a class="tasty-link" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-tasty-links-no-disclosure href="https://amzn.to/46npaOt">stand mixer</a></li>



<li><a class="tasty-link" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-tasty-links-no-disclosure href="https://amzn.to/3EzOxkl">Baking sheets</a></li>



<li><a class="tasty-link" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-tasty-links-no-disclosure href="https://amzn.to/3PUuOT2">Parchment paper</a></li>



<li>Cooling rack</li>



<li>Small <a class="tasty-link" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-tasty-links-no-disclosure href="https://amzn.to/47kK15z">spatula</a></li>



<li>Measuring cups</li>



<li>Measuring spoons</li>
</ul>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" id="h-how-to-make-chocolate-spice-cookies-tetu">How to Make Chocolate Spice Cookies (Tetu)</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1333" height="2000" data-pin-url="https://coleycooks.com/chocolate-spice-cookies/?tp_image_id=80583" data-pin-title="Sicilian Chocolate Spice Cookies" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1333&#039;%20height=&#039;2000&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201333%202000&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Four-step collage showing the process of making the chocolate spice cookie dough, from creaming shortening to adding dry ingredients, folding in walnuts, and mixing into a thick chocolate dough." class="wp-image-80583 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/1-5.png" data-srcset="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/1-5.png 1333w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/1-5-200x300.png 200w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/1-5-682x1024.png 682w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/1-5-768x1152.png 768w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/1-5-1024x1536.png 1024w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/1-5-720x1080.png 720w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/1-5-360x540.png 360w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/1-5-180x270.png 180w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/1-5-150x225.png 150w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1333px) 100vw, 1333px" /></figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" id="h-make-the-cookie-dough">Make the Cookie Dough</h3>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Preheat the oven to 375°F and line two baking sheets with parchment paper.</li>



<li>Add the shortening, oil and sugar to a <a class="tasty-link" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener" target="_blank" data-tasty-links-no-disclosure href="https://amzn.to/4hGawIE">large bowl</a> and mix to combine, then mix in the eggs one at a time.</li>



<li>Add the flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, salt, walnuts and chocolate chips (if using), then mix until combined.</li>
</ol>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1333" height="2000" data-pin-url="https://coleycooks.com/chocolate-spice-cookies/?tp_image_id=80584" data-pin-title="Sicilian Chocolate Spice Cookies" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1333&#039;%20height=&#039;2000&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201333%202000&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Four-step collage showing cocoa in a bowl, then adding powdered sugar and milk, mixing into a glossy chocolate frosting, and whipping until smooth and fluffy." class="wp-image-80584 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2-5.png" data-srcset="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2-5.png 1333w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2-5-200x300.png 200w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2-5-682x1024.png 682w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2-5-768x1152.png 768w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2-5-1024x1536.png 1024w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2-5-720x1080.png 720w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2-5-360x540.png 360w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2-5-180x270.png 180w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2-5-150x225.png 150w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1333px) 100vw, 1333px" /></figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" id="h-make-the-icing-nbsp">Make the Icing&nbsp;</h3>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Add the melted butter to a bowl, then stir in the cocoa until smooth and glossy.</li>



<li>Add half of the powdered sugar, then half of the milk and beat until combined. Add the remaining powdered sugar and milk, then beat until smooth and spreadable. Stir in the vanilla.</li>
</ol>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_8df073-b7"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<p class="has-text-align-left"><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> If your icing doesn't have the right consistency, add enough milk to smooth it out or more powdered sugar to thicken it.</p>
</div></div>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1333" height="2000" data-pin-url="https://coleycooks.com/chocolate-spice-cookies/?tp_image_id=80585" data-pin-title="Sicilian Chocolate Spice Cookies" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1333&#039;%20height=&#039;2000&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201333%202000&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Four-step collage showing rolling the dough into balls on parchment, baked cookies on the tray, spreading chocolate frosting on top, and a tray of fully frosted cookies with optional walnut toppings." class="wp-image-80585 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/3-4.png" data-srcset="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/3-4.png 1333w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/3-4-200x300.png 200w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/3-4-682x1024.png 682w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/3-4-768x1152.png 768w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/3-4-1024x1536.png 1024w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/3-4-720x1080.png 720w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/3-4-360x540.png 360w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/3-4-180x270.png 180w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/3-4-150x225.png 150w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1333px) 100vw, 1333px" /></figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" id="h-bake-and-assemble">Bake and Assemble</h3>



<ol id="isPasted" class="wp-block-list">
<li>Pinch off pieces and roll into 1-inch balls. Arrange on the baking sheets with slight space between them. They will not spread much.</li>
</ol>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_b503ea-08"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<p class="has-text-align-left"><strong>Pro Tip: </strong>If the chocolate dough feels sticky, chill it briefly so it's easier to roll into smooth dough balls. You can coat your hands in a little bit of oil when rolling into balls to keep it from sticking to your hands.&nbsp;</p>
</div></div>



<ol start="2" class="wp-block-list">
<li>Bake until the cookies look set, puffed and dry on the surface but still feel soft when gently pressed, about 10-15 minutes.</li>



<li>Cool completely before icing so the frosting sets rather than melting.</li>



<li>Spread the icing over the cooled cookies with a small spatula or knife.</li>



<li>While the icing is still soft, press a walnut half on top if desired. Let the icing set before storing.</li>
</ol>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_e1d5de-a1"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column18787_44fdbe-4f"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col"></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_6836fe-fa"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<h2 class="kt-adv-heading80574_eef4a2-e8 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading80574_eef4a2-e8">Tips for Success</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Walnuts are optional but I love them. Use very finely chopped walnuts in the dough and add walnut halves on top for a classic look. Toasted walnuts will have an even better flavor!</li>



<li>Shortening is traditional and what my family uses, but you can substitute butter. Use 1 cup unsalted butter at room temperature and expect a slightly harder cookie.</li>



<li>The icing consistency should be thick yet spreadable. Adjust with more milk or powdered sugar until it reaches the desired consistency.</li>



<li>Let the tops of the cookies cool completely on a <a class="tasty-link" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-tasty-links-no-disclosure href="https://amzn.to/3FKrILF">wire rack</a> before icing or the chocolate frosting will melt.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column18787_44fdbe-4f"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col"></div></div>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_495b2c-b0"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<h2 class="kt-adv-heading80574_e18961-a2 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading80574_e18961-a2">Variations</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Add sprinkles on the top of each cookie for a festive look.</li>



<li>Add a little bit of orange zest to the dough for a citrus twist.</li>



<li>Shape the cookie dough into smaller portions for gifting.</li>



<li>Replace the walnuts for other classic Italian nuts like pistachios, almonds or hazelnuts.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1799" data-pin-url="https://coleycooks.com/chocolate-spice-cookies/?tp_image_id=80581" data-pin-title="Sicilian Chocolate Spice Cookies" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1200&#039;%20height=&#039;1799&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201200%201799&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A bitten chocolate spice cookie showing the soft center with chopped walnuts, surrounded by other frosted cookies." class="wp-image-80581 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-18.jpg" data-srcset="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-18.jpg 1200w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-18-200x300.jpg 200w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-18-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-18-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-18-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-18-720x1079.jpg 720w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-18-360x540.jpg 360w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-18-180x270.jpg 180w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-18-150x225.jpg 150w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_9da3f7-79"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<h2 class="kt-adv-heading80574_ecc285-48 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading80574_ecc285-48">Serving Suggestions</h2>



<p>Serve these Italian cookies with an assortment of other cookies like my rich&nbsp;<a href="https://coleycooks.com/chocolate-espresso-cookies/">Chocolate Espresso Shortbread Cookies</a>, these&nbsp;<a href="https://coleycooks.com/chocolate-dipped-peanut-butter-cookies/">Chocolate Dipped Peanut Butter Cookies</a>&nbsp;or fudgy&nbsp;<a href="https://coleycooks.com/tiramisu-brownies/">Tiramisu Brownies</a>.&nbsp;</p>



<p>They're perfect with a nice cup of coffee for a simple treat. For special occasions, serve them with a classic&nbsp;<a href="https://coleycooks.com/italian-affogato-recipe/">Italian Affogato</a>.</p>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_0c2692-4e"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<h2 class="kt-adv-heading80574_79e7a5-53 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading80574_79e7a5-53">&nbsp;How to Store Italian Chocolate Spice Cookies</h2>



<p>Store the cookies in an airtight container at room temperature for up to 1 week. Freeze in single layers separated by parchment paper for up to 2 months. Thaw at room temperature before serving.</p>



<p>These also cookies freeze really well! You can freeze them already baked and frosted, or you can freeze the dough. Thaw overnight in the refrigerator.</p>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" data-pin-url="https://coleycooks.com/chocolate-spice-cookies/?tp_image_id=80578" data-pin-title="Sicilian Chocolate Spice Cookies" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1200&#039;%20height=&#039;800&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201200%20800&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A close up of a chocolate spice cookie topped with thick chocolate frosting and chopped walnuts on parchment paper." class="wp-image-80578 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-14.jpg" data-srcset="https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-14.jpg 1200w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-14-300x200.jpg 300w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-14-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-14-768x512.jpg 768w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-14-720x480.jpg 720w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-14-360x240.jpg 360w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-14-180x120.jpg 180w, https://coleycooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/italian-chocolate-spice-cookies-14-150x100.jpg 150w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" id="h-faqs">FAQs</h2>



<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1643652919521"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>What makes these Italian chocolate spice cookies different from other Italian chocolate cookies?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">This version uses a creamed mixture of shortening and oil, plenty of warm spices, and the option for chopped walnuts or chocolate chips. It bakes into soft cookies with a tender texture, then gets finished with a simple chocolate frosting that sets into a smooth, sweet layer. It's a family recipe that's comforting and familiar while still keeping the spirit of the classic Sicilian cookie. The spices make it perfect for Christmastime!</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1713981424124"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Why is my cookie dough too sticky to roll?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Sticky dough usually means the dry ingredients weren't fully absorbed. Letting the dough rest a few minutes helps, or you can chill it briefly. Avoid adding extra purpose flour unless absolutely necessary. If it's still sticky, coat your hands in a little bit of oil or shortening before rolling. </p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1764797117327"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>How do I freeze the cookie dough?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Scoop and roll the dough into dough balls, then freeze them on a cookie sheet until solid. Transfer to plastic wrap or an airtight container. Bake from frozen, adding a little bit of extra time if needed.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1764797128426"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Can I add other types of chocolate?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Yes. You can fold in chocolate chips or chopped up chocolate bars to these delicious cookies or experiment with different types of chocolate to adjust the chocolate flavor. Just avoid adding too much or the dough may not hold together well.</p> </div> </div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_0abdf6-81"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column80574_ef32fe-ee"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" id="h-related-recipes">Related Recipes</h2>


